<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-30T08:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-30T08:40:00-05:00" n="767" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115/20T: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-30T15:00:00+01:20">August 30,
                                    1939—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 30—11:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>143. Personal for the Under Secretary. Will you please give me some
                            information concerning suggestions with respect to eventual arrangements
                            for free entry of goods into Rotterdam and Antwerp which I understand
                            the President made in conversations he had yesterday with the Dutch
                            Minister and the Belgian Ambassador?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gordon</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>